Tech lead in Document App project responsible for scoping the requirement, drafting and designing the system architecture, planning and dividing tasks, and, lastly, implementing all the code both frontend and backend. The project goal is to achieve a customizable document template for generating a PDF document. This feature is used across a broad platform such as issuing an order invoice or summarizing shop sales reports. This feature become one of the key features of our platform

Other than implementing features, I also help out maintaining a coding standard and guiding new joiners to get used to our system as soon as possible. Sometimes, I also jump into improving our platform to make them more friendly to the developer and reduce downtime on blocking the pipeline.

Our current tech stack is one of the most amazing to work on. Here, we use Typescript with GraphQL, Prisma, and serverless. In this combination, you can certainly barely find any tutorial online. It has a lot of benefits, but while has some downsides as well. For me, it allows me to have a very clear picture of what is a backend both overall and in detail.
Lastly, found myself to have very good investigating skills. This help identifies the source of problems very fast and precisely. But to do so, it may require a lot of understanding and experience. This is one of the tasks that most people avoid but for me, it is very enjoyable. And, I do like to hop into helping others when they are struck by some problem for a while. After successfully tracking down the root cause, I feel proud for me to be able to accelerate other’s work🚀.
